          Full Job Description

As a fundraiser officer, you will support the company from a fundraising & proposal writing perspective. You will work alongside Eva Teekens (Chief Investment Officer) and the Portfolio Managers and support the fundraising activities of reNature, both for the foundation as for the company. The primary responsibility will be on scoping for funding opportunities such as prizes, call for proposals and challenges, coordinating with portfolio managers and applying for these funds by writing proposals. Next to this, you will support the Chief Investment Officer where needed.

reNature Profile

We believe nature and agriculture can cooperate instead of compete. We also believe that farmers and local communities across the globe deserve a long-term profitable future. That’s why we focus on Regenerative Agroforestry, an agricultural system with three impact fields:

- Environmental impact: increase in soil carbon, biodiversity, water storage and forests preservation.

- Social impact: food security and sovereignty, next gen farmers motivation, rural development and women empowerment.

- Economic impact: less external input costs, different income streams due to diversification as well as potentially yield increase.

With our international team based in Amsterdam and Brazil, we build model farms and model schools on all scales and all around the globe. Our goal is to regenerate 1 million hectares of land worldwide and ensure food security for over 10 million farmers & communities by 2030.

Duties & Responsibilities

- Responsible for identifying project funding opportunities;
- Getting feedback from Portfolio Managers and understand individual project needs;
- Writing, applying and submitting proposals for funding; and
- Supporting the CIO where needed.

Requirements

The ideal candidate will be well-versed in writing proposals and will have affinity with agricultural funding in developing countries.
Ideally, the candidate has studied environmental studies, business studies or any other relevant study to the position being posted.

- Ability to write concise and informative proposals;
- Strong copywriting skills in English and proposal writing affinity;
- Ability to work under pressure and plan personal workload effectively;
- Right to Work: Must have legal right to work in the Netherlands;
- Languages: Dutch & English is as a must. A third language such as Spanish, French or Portuguese is a plus.

Competencies:

- Must be analytical and inquisitive;
- Must be passionate about working in a multifunction startup & task-oriented team management;
- Must be able to engage with staff at all levels of the organisation and exercise sound judgement;
- Must be a good copy-writer & clearly communicate objectives;
- Must be inspired by a shared vision;
- Must have team building skills;
- Must be cool under pressure and empathetic;
- Must be competent & organized with scheduling;
- Must be able to deliver high-quality proposals seeking to attract funds;
- Must display a cohesive ability at interpersonal and communication skills, both verbally and written;

Supervision:

The supervision will be done by Eva Teekens (CIO).

Duration:

The duration of the contract will be for six months. With the intention to extend when it expires.




